Eric Risberg Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado 
Emiliano Grillo, of Argentina, follows his shot from the seventh tee of the Silverado Resort North Course during the final round of the Frys.com golf tournament Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Napa, Calif. (AP Photo/Eric Risberg) Eric Risberg Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado 
Justin Thomas looks over the second green of the Silverado Resort North Course during the final round of the Frys.com golf tournament Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Napa, Calif. (AP Photo/Eric Risberg) Eric Risberg Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado 
Kevin Na, left, and Jason Bohn, right, line up their putts on the second green of the Silverado Resort North Course during the final round of the Frys.com golf tournament Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Napa, Calif. (AP Photo/Eric Risberg) Eric Risberg Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado 
Justin Rose, of England, makes a 55-foot birdie putt on the second green of the Silverado Resort North Course during the final round of the Frys.com golf tournament Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Napa, Calif. (AP Photo/Eric Risberg) Eric Risberg Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado 
Brendan Steele chips down to the third green of the Silverado Resort North Course during the final round of the Frys.com golf tournament Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Napa, Calif. (AP Photo/Eric Risberg) Posted: Sunday, October 18, 2015 9:55 pm | Updated: 11:02 pm, Sun Oct 18, 2015. Grillo wins in rookie debut at Silverado Associated Press | 
NAPA, Calif. (AP) — Emiliano Grillo of Argentina won his PGA Tour rookie debut Sunday at the Frys.com Open by holing a 25-foot birdie putt on the 18th for a 3-under 69, and then making the most out of a second chance in the playoff to beat Kevin Na. 
Nearly as impressive as his closing birdie was the way the 23-year-old Argentine bounced back from a shocking miss.
